This paper focuses on energy-efficient multicast scheduling in mmWave small cells, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of device-to-device (D2D) communications and concurrent transmissions, which are related to system design and control. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of millimeter wave (mmWave) bands, which is a topic related to multimedia and image processing. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the roles of D2D communications and concurrent transmissions, which is related to distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category.
